games.comment: Frank Gore led the team with 4 receptions for 55 yards. Vernon Davis and Bryant Johnson registeredthree catches each.    The only bright spot for Mike Martz's offense was that Frank Gore rushed for 96 yards and a touchdown. However, he received just 14 carries in typical Martz style.    The man who used to play for Mike Martz wasn't spectacular, but was efficient enough to win on the road, which is something the Cardinals couldn't do last year.
Frank Gore ran for 51 yards on 17 carries with 3 receptions for 26 yards.    Savage completed 19-of-44 passes for 219 yards with a score. Hopkins had 6 reception for 86 yards and a score.
